                  Vnum enim fuit, & ſemel oblatum, & ſufficit in ſempiternum, ad tollenda omnia peccata Credentium; This one Sacrifice, once offered, ſufficed for euer, to take away all the Sinnes of the faithfull.

No leſſe, or greater Seuerity, was extended againſt Apoſtates, by the ancient Decrees of Chriſtian Emperors; They Cod. lib. 1. tit. 10 Si quis lege 3. Hi qui Sanctam
confiſcated their Goods, they were depriued of the ordinary ciuill Priuiledges of Chriſtians, they might not ſucceed in Inheritance, or bee made heyres of the Goods or Lands of their Parents, they were baniſhed into moſt remote Territories;
they were neuer to returne backe, nor to recouer their former Priuiledges.

